From bam Subject The Bob Dylan Baseball Abstract Just a little something I found while reading the Village Voice which is not noted for its sports coverage but occasionally the print some interesting This year the predictions team analyses for the season were presented in the form of Bob Dylan I don't have the article in front of me so I'll only give the memorable ones here that I remember and know the melody I could dig up more if there is Yankess to the tune of Subterranean Homesick Blues Howe is in the basement mixing up the George is on the pavement thinking 'bout the Wade Boggs in a trench coat bat out paid off Says he's got a bad back wants to get it laid Look out kids it's somethin' you Don't know when but it's Columbus Mets to the tune of Like a Rolling Stone Once upon a time you played so fine you threw away Dykstra before his prime didn't you People said Beware Cone he's bound to roam But you thought they were just kidding You used to laugh about The Strawberry that was headin' But now you don't talk so loud Now you don't seem so proud About having to shop Vince Coleman for your next Phillies to the tune of Highway Well Daulton and Dykstra should have some fun Just keep them off of Highway Giants to the tune of The Ballad of Rubin 'Hurricane' Carter This is the story of the Magowan The man Petersburg came to pan For something that he never done He's sit in the owner's box but Day he could have the Tampian of the world